    "updated_at": "2017-05-19T07:31:41Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Double clicking a unit and hotkey work the same way, except:\r\n- hotkey excludes dead actors and selects actors on map instead of on screen if no new units are selected on screen at first +\r\nThe important difference in usage of this feature is that double click targets 1 unit - 1 owner, type; hotkey targets more units - more owners and types. We simply ignore other actors than actors of current player.\r\n\r\nFor (All players view) spectators, should we select all units of all these owners or restrict this feature for only  1 unit selection or only selections where all units belong to the same owner?\r\n~IMO it is sufficient/simplest for hotkey to support in this case only 1 unit selection like for double click so owner is known.~ It is fine to check if all selected units belong to the same owner only if spectating.\r\n\r\n"
  },
